==Romanian==
===Etymology===
An imitative substratum word, akin to Albanian ''[[pupëzë]]''. Other languages show similar forms, compare Latin ''[[upupa]]'', Sardinian ''[[pubùsa]]'', ''[[pupùsa]]'', etc.
===Noun===
'''pupăză''' ''f'' (pl. ''pupeze'')

# [[hoopoe]]
# [[garrulous]] person

===Derived terms===
*[[pupăzoi]]
*[[pupezele]]

